   <h1>Re: [VB] Bus Depot Order Follow-Up</h1>
   <b>&quot;Dave&quot; &lt;brooksdj_at_earthlink_dot_net&gt;</b><br/>
   <i>2001-12-20 22:10:46+00</i><br/>
   <br/>
   <pre>Ron is correct in that I messed up on the dates.  It was Dec and not Nov.  I
want to make sure everyone understands that the order placed on the 7th was
completed and shipped in good time for a company.  The order I problems with
before was corrected and an expectable apology was made.  The other item was
more then likely a cross in numbers since there was no message on my machine
and I was home that evening.

Dave
----- Original Message -----
From: "The Bus Depot" <busdepot_at_busdepot_dot_com>
To: "Dave" <brooksdj_at_earthlink_dot_net>; <vintagebus_at_type2_dot_com>
Sent: Thursday, December 20, 2001 4:27 PM
Subject: RE: [VB] Bus Depot Order Follow-Up


> >  I took folks advice about calling to check availability of parts that I
> needed soon.
> > Young man on the phone was polite and informed me (8 Nov) that the
> Jackpoint I
> > needed was  available for shipping.  Well,  today I thinking "it was
> available" it should
> > be here by now.  Guess what, the order was cancelled and I WAS NOT
> CONTACTED.
>
>
> Dave,
>
> It was actually recently (December, not November) when you placed the
order.
> Perhaps the jackpoint sold out between the time that you called to check
> stock, and the time that your order was entered/processed.  If there are
> only one or two of an item in stock, this can of course happen.
>
> That said, it is not true that you were not contacted.  In fact, I can
even
> tell you WHEN you were contacted. At approximately 5 pm E.S.T. on Friday,
> December 14, Mike left a message on your voice mail to say that the item
was
> out of stock for at least a month, and that you'd be best off re-ordering.
> Before doing this, he spent quite a while calling around to other
> distributors first, in the hope that he could still locate one for you
> elsewhere and have it dropshipped to you at our additional expense.  But
> unfortunately all of our suppliers were also out of stock, since the
> backorder originated from the manufacturer.  When he left that message, he
> immediately documented in your customer file both the date and the reason
> for his call to you, which is why I know all of this with such certainty.
(I
> have been insisting that my employees do so, just so I can check up on
this
> sort of complaint. So I researched it and indeed found the record of the
> call. I even spoke to Mike myself just to be absolutely sure and he
> specifically remembered leaving the message.)
>
> Then, when you called today, Paul (whom you spoke to this time) also told
> you that Mike had previously tried to contact you about it, since he saw
and
> repeated to you the same documentation that I am reading now.  So before
you
> sent this email, you ALREADY know that we HAD in fact tried to reach you
> about this.
>
> Perhaps you inadvertantly overlooked or erased the message on your machine
> or voice mail, or if there is more than one member of your household,
> perhaps someone else got it and forgot to pass it on to you.  I would also
> be more than happy to confirm your phone number with you via p-mail if you
> think there is any possibility that we have it wrong (although this would
be
> a long shot).
>
> So, I do apologize for any inconvenience caused by the fact that the item
> sold out.  I do understand your disappointment.  But we did attempt to
> contact you about it, and in fact left you a message.
>
> - Ron Salmon
>   The Bus Depot, Inc.
>   (215) 234-VWVW
>   www.busdepot_dot_com
>
>
></pre>


